					<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr"><p>Link to the course's <a href="/wiki/index.php/Statreasoning-001:Main" title="Statreasoning-001:Main">Main Page</a></p>
<h1> <span class="mw-headline" id="Definition">Definition</span></h1>
<p>A <strong>population</strong> is the entire group of entities for which at least one characteristic shall be surveyed. </p>
<h1> <span class="mw-headline" id="Contextualization">Contextualization</span></h1>
<p>In most cases an investigation including all entities is not feasible. The investigation is then constrained to a <a href="/wiki/index.php/Statreasoning-001:Sample" title="Statreasoning-001:Sample">sample</a> aiming to infer characteristics of the population from those characteristics determined for the sample.</p>

